  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-04-19",
    "date": "2021-06-11T14:55:50Z",
    "text": "Climate Risk Disclosure Act of 2021\n\nThis bill directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to\u00a0require an issuer of securities to annually disclose information regarding climate change-related risks posed to the issuer, including an issuer's strategies and actions to mitigate these risks.\n\nSpecifically, issuers must report their direct and indirect greenhouse-gas emissions and disclose their fossil fuel-related assets."
